Tethys Τηθύς   sea goddess, Titan daughter of Uranus and Gaia, brother Titan Oceanus

Nahoreiner
   Mitanni[1] during the New Kingdom period of the 18th Dynasty.
Nairi (Armenian: Նայիրի in TAO or Նաիրի in RAO) was the Assyrian name (KUR.KUR Na-i-ri, also Na-'i-ru) for a Proto-Armenian (Hurrian-speaking) tribe in the Armenian Highlands

Maasai phrase Enkare Nairobi, which translates to "cool water"
